# aiis-signatures is a security-signature CORPUS. Every file under signatures/ is a
# detection PATTERN: it definitionally contains the injection / role-inject / stego /
# exfil strings it is meant to detect, and tests/fixtures/ holds verbatim attack
# samples. Running a scanner (HackMyAgent) over this repo therefore flags the signature
# and fixture content as the very attacks it catches -- the test/-playground
# false-positive class. Suppress those paths so scanner noise does not mask a genuine
# finding elsewhere. Non-signature code (tests/validate/, schema/, .github/) stays fully
# scanned.
#
# Format (HackMyAgent): a bare line is a path prefix; a !-prefixed line is a check-ID
# pattern (exact or trailing *). Comments start with #.

signatures/
tests/fixtures/

# The CHANGELOG documents attack techniques with verbatim samples (e.g. a zero-width-
# joiner evasion example under v0.2.1), so it intentionally carries invisible /
# adversarial codepoints that the unicode-stego checks flag.
CHANGELOG.md
